    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Can this be used with the Hits widget? Here's a rough outline of my code, the code you've linked to doesn't work as expected with my example\"\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst productSearch = instantsearch({\r\n    appId: 'xxx',\r\n    apiKey: 'xxx',\r\n    indexName: 'products',\r\n    routing: true\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar hitsWidget = instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n    container: '#product-results',\r\n    autoHideContainer: true,\r\n    searchParameters: {\r\n        hitsPerPage: 4,\r\n    },\r\n    templates: {\r\n        empty: 'No results',\r\n        allItems: '{{{_highlightResult.description.value}}}'\r\n    }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar configWidget = instantsearch.widgets.configure({\r\n    attributesToSnippet: ['description:5'], // 5 words, still highlighted\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar searchInput = instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({\r\n    container: '#search',\r\n    placeholder: 'Search for products'\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nproductSearch.addWidget(hitsWidget);\r\nproductSearch.addWidget(configWidget);\r\nproductSearch.addWidget(searchInput);\r\nproductSearch.start();\r\n```",
